ds can do a huge variety of tasks, and the key to playing a good bard is deciding which of those to do in each situation, a decision a typical bard must make every 3 seconds.<br>
<br>
Using Glasya's list only because it brings up some good points...<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1. 1-hit wonder (twists 1 song, worst if that 1 song fall in any category below)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Any moderately decent bard should be singing multiple songs the majority of the time during battle.  However, just because you only see one flashing icon on your buff bar doesn't mean he is a 1-hit wonder.  Many players turned off their bard song spam a long time ago and are completely oblivious to much of what I am doing unless it creates an icon on their screen.  I've been in groups where I'm very busy slowing / snaring / debuffing / mezzing / charming and then get yelled at because somebody didn't see any flashing icons on their screen /boggle.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2. plays haste when a chanter is casting haste, bard haste and chanter/shaman haste do not stack, the only benefit to playing a haste song is the stat bonuses, but instead there are several stat songs without haste that are better</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Bard haste songs are definitely a little tricky.  We have many haste songs, and they all stack a little differently with enc/shm hastes and even other bard hastes.  Many of our haste songs do buff some other stats as well.  There have been a few ocassions growing up as a bard where I chose to play a haste song for the stat buffs, fully knowing the haste would not stack with the enc/shm in the group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3. not playing mana song in down time or not asking for mana status so that it can be played full time</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
For most good bards, firing up mana-song as a fight ends is second nature.  There are situations where this might not be the best thing to do though.  For example, if more than a couple group members are missing hp, it's often a good idea to twist in a pulse of regen with the mana.  A major pet peeve of bards is when people ask for mana song when it is already playing (at low levels the bard mana song gives no icon).  Also, it's a little irritating when a caster demands mana-song in the middle of a battle when I am doing half-a-dozen other things which are far more beneficial to the group then giving you a few more points of mana (especially if the demander is a wiz/mag/other non-healing caster).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 4. not using a woodwind when mezzing and having a hard time</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Most bards I know don't bother with a woodwind.  I usually won't bother myself unless I get a couple resists in a row, in which case I will sometimes whip out the flute.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 5. not snaring/slowing when you have runners and no snarer/darker</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A good bard should be doing this, but if someone else in the group can do it also, it should be agreed between them who's responsibility it is.  If there is no slower in the group, a bard will often take this responsibility, since our snare songs have a slow component as well.  If a shm is slowing, it often makes more sense to let a dru/rng/etc do the snaring to free up the bard's twist for another song.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 6. not interrupting casters with mez song when they try to CH/gate/etc</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Yes, bards should be doing this, although it can be challenging to figure out how to bring this into the rhythym of your twist quickly and recover afterwards the first few times.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 7. not knowing what some utility songs are and why they are needed (rune song, magic rune, agi/rune, etc)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
There are a ton of utility songs and a good bard should know what ALL of them do and be able to incorporate them into the twist when they make sense.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 8. not knowing how songs stack</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Song stacking is complicated and is learned by most bards through trial and error.  How songs stack with other caster spells and even other bard songs can be confusing, especially when the order matters.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 9. not being able to twist more that 2 songs, 5+ is nice but 3 is standard. If you don't know how to twist 5+ then you haven't played a bard long enough (think Amplification and BOH...  )</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Getting 3 songs in the twist is doable for any bard with a decent connection.  Remember, just because you don't see 3 flashing icons doesn't mean the bard isn't doing 3 or even more.  On a good connection in a fairly lag-free zone, I can twist 4 pretty reliably, but the timing takes more attention and will exhaust you after a while.  With regard to Glasya's 5+ twist, it's not really a twist in my opinion.  Amplification is a song that lasts 5 ticks (most songs last 3) but does not show up on anyone's screen other than the bard (when up, it increases the effectiveness of singing based songs).  BoH is the Breath of Harmony, a weapon which has a clickable song on it which lasts a couple minutes.  So yes, you can have 5+ songs going simultaneously, but not in what I would call a twist.  Also, we don't all have BoHs to play with <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   One more thing to note:  there is a class of bad bards out there who try to make themselves look like good bards by getting as many icons flashing on their group's buff bars as possible.  It is far better for a group when the bard is twisting the RIGHT 3 songs than the WRONG 5+ songs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2. Haste = item + spell/song + vah-shir(battlecry or warsong) + ervaj<br>
that's the formula, no one sings ervaj since a brass item is required, vah-shir songs were bugged for a while where they actually acted as slow if you have no other haste on you (rollover bug) which was fixed, this is the only one that can be used with utility when you have a chanter or shaman doing haste.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This is all correct as far as I know.  By &quot;ervaj&quot;, Glasya means either of two songs, Melody of Ervaj (50) or Composition of Ervaj (60), and yes they are rarely played, although I have played with it in the right situation.  The Vah-Shir songs are still bugged in the way Glasya mentions.  If a player has no other haste on them (item, enc/shm spell, other bard song), then the Vah-Shir songs will act like a slow.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> How many bards actually know what Katta's Song of Sworddancing does... unless they look it up many do not know.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  This song is a buff which increases group member's dexterity and adds a proc to their primary weapon (yes, fists work too).  The proc debuffs the mobs dex by 25 points.  Some groups think it's a waste like Loy above, but I have just as many groups who absolutely love it.  The dex buff makes weapons proc more, rogue backstabs land more often, and melee skill increases come more easily.  The dex debuff proc makes a mob flurry/proc less, when applicable.  Currently, I can buff dex by 95 points with this song and my drum.  It also has this funny little bug:  when you play it, the monks in your group will get Tiger Claw skill increases for no apparent reason <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> How many know it is more efficient to twist Canata and 2 pulses of Mana song rather than play one by itself.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Actually, if you want to maximize mana regen, you should keep Amplification up in this twist as well.  If your connection allows a 3-twist, this amounts to (Cantata / Amp / Mana / Cantata / Mana / Mana / Repeat).  If you can do a 4-twist, throw another Mana between the Cantata pulses.  On this note however, twisting can be very exhausting, especially after doing it straight for several hours.  Many bards will choose to not twist between battles to give their fingers a rest and just turn on mana by itself.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> How many know that effects of an instrument is valid for a pulse while instrument is held, if one is required only first pulse is checked rest are processed as if it was played without one. Play McVaxus with Horn for 1 pulse ,then stop song and remove instrument and watch the effect get halved (or whatever multiplier you have). So twisting a resist song with drum, then swapping instruments will result in half power song for ticks when instrument it needs in not in place.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
If I am understanding you correctly Glasya, I think you are mistaken on this count.  Most songs last 3 ticks.  If you have the proper instrument equipped on the first tick (i.e. when the song &quot;lands&quot;), you can safely remove the instrument and turn off the song.  The full benefit of the instrument will be in effect for the other 2 ticks.  I just tested this myself with Elemental Rhythyms to be sure.  I equipped drum, started song, let the first pulse hit, then stopped song and removed drum.  The drum-enhanced resists stayed constant for all 3 ticks until the song wore off.  Maybe I'm misunderstanding what you are trying to say here.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if you don't read the rest of this post, at least remember this:  Bards are complicated and difficult to play well; there are good bards and bad bards out there.  However, be sure you know what you are talking about before you go criticizing or ordering a bard around.  The benefits of a bard are powerful, but sometimes subtle.<br>
<br>
No one will probably read this, but I feel better having written it hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Rabatha Talechaser<br>
Minstrel of the 53rd Ditty <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/ulollwislom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loll Wislom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle> 1    Poster<BR><TABLE WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=7 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR HEIGHT=5><TD WIDTH=2 BGCOLOR=#ffff00></TD><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#ffff00></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#ffff00></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15></TD><TD WIDTH=2></TD></TR><TR HEIGHT=2><TD WIDTH=2 BGCOLOR=#000080></TD><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#000080></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#000080></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#000080></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#000080></TD><TD WIDTH=1 BGCOLOR=#222222></TD><TD WIDTH=15 BGCOLOR=#000080></TD><TD WIDTH=2></TD></TR></TABLE></span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/17/02 6:16:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Hating Mofo's</span><hr size=1> I know nothing of bards from first hand short of this.  I have had some mighty BIG trains started from bad tranfer of agro. Bards playing AE "agresive" songs will agro through walls.. Call it game bug I call it not knowing your stuff.  There are zones I cant use AE ... Like Hate or parts of CT.  I sugest that the brads think on this.  /petition normaly works since the GMs know what a bard can do.  Last train was in chardo we had slave drivers and red dogs in the Obsever spawn.... We were making jokes about the doggy door when we kill the red dog half way out of the wall.... Then the 15 pull made it not so funny.<br>
