<br>
Lets take a look at this statement shall we?<br>
<br>
Verses of Victory (L50)<br>
Party: Increase Strength (30) <br>
Party: Increase Agility (30) <br>
Party: Increase Attack Speed (30%) <br>
Party: Increase AC (15)<br>
<br>
What do we have other than this that raises melee stats?<br>
<br>
Nillipus' March of the Wee(L52)<br>
Party: Increase Armor Class by 10 <br>
Party: Increase Agility by 18 <br>
Party: Increase Absorb Damage Shield by 12 <br>
(Note this buff drops as soon as you take 12 or more damage - think of it as being chain runed every 18 seconds for 12 hp)<br>
<br>
McVaxius Berserker Crescendo (L42)<br>
Party: Increase Strength (15 - 30) <br>
Party: Increase Attack Speed (+20%)<br>
<br>
Vilia's Verses of Celerity(L36)<br>
Party: Increase Agility (23-30) <br>
Party: Increase Attack Speed (+15%) <br>
<br>
Anthem De Arms(L10)<br>
Party: Increase Strength (10-30) <br>
Party: Increase Attack Speed (10%) <br>
<br>
Chant of Battle(L1)<br>
Party: Increase Str (5-25) <br>
Party: Increase Dex (5-25) <br>
Party: Increase AC (1-7) <br>
<br>
So which would you pick? Thats right - one WITH haste. In fact its not until level 57 (Mcvaxius' Rousing Rondo) that you even get another song that is even similar - and any bard that can get to 57 should have at least some idea of how to play the class, right? (all numbers taken fom castersrealm)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 3. not playing mana song in down time or not asking for mana status so that it can be played full time<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yes mana song should be the first thing a bard does during downtime. But when you are in a non-stop exp hungry group, when do you get downtime? very rarely. During the fight? You really think the small amount of mana you are going to get from a bard song during the length of one fight is going to make-or-break the encounter? Especially compaired to the other benefits the bard is bringing the rest of the group? Mana song was designed for DOWNTIME - you cant learn to conserve mana, play a non-casting class (try playing a bard, and see how annoying it gets being asked for mana song 15 times a day, when you have been singing it for the last 5 minutes - even the version WITH an icon).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 4. not using a woodwind when mezzing and having a hard time<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
99% of the time, I have no trouble mezzing a mob without an instrument. The times I do have trouble, even with an instrument, and all my charisma gear, I find it still doesnt help THAT much. I can only recall once having to resort to using an instrument while mezzing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 5. not snaring/slowing when you have runners and no snarer/darker<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Sometimes you are fighting mobs that hit FAST. You have a shaman/enchanter, but no snarer. Better to root, and have a shaman slow, than have a bard snare/slow (you are aware our song is only approx 35% snare/30%slow). Im not saying all situations, just there are times when using bard snare is not the best solution.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 9. not being able to twist more that 2 songs, 5+ is nice but 3 is standard. If you don't know how to twist 5+ then you haven't played a bard long enough (think Amplification and BOH...  )<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Amplification: This song increases the impact of songs which use the Singing skill. All spells used while this is in effect get a flat % bonus. The exact amount is not known though. For example: If a song gives 10 mana per tick, and amplification adds 10% then it will give 11 mana instead. If it gives 50% then it would add 15% per tick. (taken from castersrealm)<br>
<br>
It does not make songs last 5 ticks. While a BoH might look like a nice addition, many bards prefer weapons with better stats. BoH goes for around 10k at the moment. Dizok Wristsnapper sells for half that MAX. both have the same damage and delay, but the WS has stats. For the duration of the time I had a BoH, trying to twist the effect of the sword into my regular twists made my songs lock up - similar to the dex song bug, before it was fixed.<br>
<br>
5 songs may be nice, but remember one thing - I may be willing to die for my group, but im not willing to spend the next week suffering from repetitive strain injury for them!<br>
<br>
There is one thing worse than a bad bard - thats someone who thinks they know how to play your class better than you. Ok, so not all bards are great - but as you can see, it takes a lot to truely master a bard, and even now at 56, im still learning. What makes people think they know how to play a bard better than someone who has spent that long actually experiencing being a bard?<br>
<br>
(Sorry if I appear to be ranting at you Glasya, but as a bard I get asked these questions all the time, and its annoying as hell to have people think they know better than me, just becasue they saw their room-mates, best friends, sister-in-laws, nephew play a bard once!) <p><center><table border="2" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="2" bordercolor="#ffffff" bgcolor="#000000"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000"><image src="http://www.cognitivedescent.co.uk/eritanna-sig.JPG"></td><td align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#000000"><a href="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm" target="_blank"><img src="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/mythresult/dragon.jpg"
border="0" width="330" height="180"></a><br><font color="#ffffff"><a
href="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm" target="_blank">What Mythological Creature Are You?</a></font></td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uglasya7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glasya7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vending Machine</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/18/02 10:02:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DEX</span><hr size=1> Just read about Amplification and it was changed, so the increase duration aspect is not listed anymore.  It is still possible to twist 4 songs with BoH which as a bard I think is way more important than even the epic.  On raids where MOBs dispell, BoH is extremely useful to keep in slot 1.  VahShir Battlecry/Warcry also last 21 seconds (almost 4 ticks). <br>
<br>
Most bards also never bother getting the SS bracer which as of now stacks with mage DS (but not druid as of last few patches) and shaman potion and bard DS song.<br>
<br>
Instrument mezzing is very useful in the planes where things have higher resists and hit too hard to screw around with a change of being resisted (even with 1050 ac).<br>
<br>
Snaring example I used, I see too often when I am not playing my bard (one of my other 50+ chars), the bards that never bother snaring (when there is no one to snare) and things run away and waste time (or get adds).  I have used my cleric to dark the MOBs too often when a bard just plays VoV or mana song and nothing else...<br>
<br>
Question as to what I would twist if there is a chanter hasting?<br>
1. March Of Wee<br>
2a. Katta if the MOBs rampage, flurry, proc, or need dex reduced for other reasons<br>
2b. psalm for DS (and resists if any)<br>
3a. Cantata if mana is needed<br>
3b. Vah Shir if more than 1 melee<br>
3c. Rondo when I get it<br>
4. BoH Niv's<br>
<br>
This is my usual 4 song setup, often I will do Amp if I am doing VoV.  If there is a shaman in the group they usually harness the tanks so I don't need to worry about str or dex, and agi from Wee is very useful then.  It all depends on the group.  It all becomes moot when the tanks start procing Avatar, then I can become a mana battery <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
