<br>
&quot;that's horrible!&quot; you say. not helping my group at all. <br>
my twist goes something like this, depending on situation<br>
amp, vov, bellow, bellow, vov, bellow<br>
or<br>
amp, vov, snare, cantata<br>
<br>
why vov you ask? don't forget amplification increases the effectiveness of songs by 80% (i think).<br>
why bellow? 50 damage a hit with amp. that's more than i melee for. helps increase damage output.<br>
Katta's is always memmed over bellow with rogue in group. The increase damage the rogue will probably get is higher than the 50 damage from bellow. <br>
all depends on situation<br>
song of dawn is good if your tank is lower level than you and you've been mezzing. a good bard can mez 4 mobs at a time. song of dawn helps remove aggro from you so you can keep mezzing.<br>
<br>
i -never- use windwood with Song of Twilight<br>
the fact that it's good for raids is pointless if you have 3 55+ chanters. my guild has 3 60 and a 58 chanter. most are usually on a raid. no point me mezzing, so song of twilight isn't even memmed. <br>
<br>
also, with a chanter AND shaman in the group, the bard should be doing haste. why?<br>
chanter can mez. shaman can buff.<br>
chanter haste at 60 - 66%<br>
shaman haste at 60 - 50%<br>
bard haste at 54 - 80% <br>
amplification + 54 haste. this is only saying that amplification increases the haste. it may not, but it SHOULD. <br>
i may be wrong tho, which means that the chanter should be doing haste. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uglasya7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glasya7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vending Machine</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/18/02 3:32:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DEX</span><hr size=1> Leave chanters to do Shissar if they have and C2 or they will throw one of many fits that chanters tend to throw for no apparent reason.  Is it me or are many enchanters just plain crazy!  Bards are bards but enchanters are nuts!   I'll start another thread for this.<br>
