<br>
Yes there are good bards, and bad ones. And it doesnt usually take long to see which they are - but a bard bard wont become a good bard without experiencing the bad stuff - like it has already been said - you cant PL a bard - it comes with practice, and ONLY practice.<br>
<br>
Next time you see a bard doing something wrong - dont knock them - they might not be that experienced yet. They might be experimenting. Dont tell them what they SHOULD be doing - That just pisses us off. Its funny how often you get people telling you how to play a 50+ bard, when you dont see that many of them around. Suggest to them instead of ways of making them more effective. Offer support and advice, and we will be much more receptive. No bard wants to be known as a bad bard...<br>
<br>
A good bard, can make a great partner. <p><center><table border="2" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="2" bordercolor="#ffffff" bgcolor="#000000"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000"><image src="http://www.cognitivedescent.co.uk/eritanna-sig.JPG"></td><td align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#000000"><a href="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm" target="_blank"><img src="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/mythresult/dragon.jpg"
